   "verification_evidence": "Modified anoxic Burk's medium was used to cultivate strains for both N fixation and DIR at 30\u00b0C. The medium contained the following components (per liter): 20 g mannitol, 0.2 g KH2PO4, 0.8 g\u00b7K2HPO4, 0.2 g MgSO4\u00b77H2O, 0.1 g CaSO4\u00b72H2O, and trace amounts of Na2MoO4\u00b72H2O and FeCl3, at pH 7.0. Fe(III) reduction was conducted in this medium supplemented with Fe(III)-citrate.",
